<p>=F0=9F=9F=A7 <strong>History of the Pythagorean Theorem</strong>: Althou=
gh <strong>it is attributed to the Greek philosopher and mathematician Pyth=
agoras (6th century B.C.)</strong>, the practical knowledge and use of this=
 relationship existed thousands of years earlier. Ancient civilizations suc=
h as the Babylonians, Egyptians, and Chinese applied it as early as around =
2000 B.C., as seen in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plimpton=
_322" rel=3D"noopener">Plimpton 322 tablet</a> from the Babylonians, who us=
ed it for practical purposes in construction and surveying.</p>
<p>Remember that the <strong>Pythagorean theorem only applies to right tria=
ngles </strong>(also called the theorem of the three squares), but it is a =
fundamental tool in geometry, trigonometry, physics, engineering, <a href=
=3D"https://ovacen.com/en/construction/">construction</a> and many scientif=
ic disciplines. Do you dare with the next exercise quiz?</p>
<div class=3D"pitagoras-quiz-container">
<h3 class=3D"pitagoras-quiz-title">Pythagorean Theorem Quiz</h3>
<div class=3D"pitagoras-quiz-formula">
