<h3><strong>Applications of the Pythagorean Theorem</strong></h3>
<p>This theorem is one of the most widely applied <strong>mathematical form=
ulas</strong>, serving as a crucial tool in various fields:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong>Architecture, engineering, construction, and design</strong>: F=
undamental for calculating distances, heights, slopes, ensuring precise rig=
ht angles in structures, and in the design of buildings, bridges, and ramps=
.</li>
<li><strong>Surveying, geodesy, and navigation</strong>: Essential for dete=
rmining horizontal and vertical distances in land surveys, map-making, rout=
e calculations, terrain inclinations, and forms the basis of measurement sy=
stems like GPS.</li>
<li><strong>Physics</strong>: Used to calculate the magnitude of resultant =
vectors, decompose forces, and compute trajectories.</li>
<li><strong>Computer science and information sciences</strong>: Its princip=
les are applied in abstract concepts to calculate distances in multidimensi=
onal spaces, relevant in areas such as facial recognition in artificial int=
elligence.</li>
</ul>
